    • Field Detail

      • testAuthUser

        public static IUser testAuthUser
        The intended user signed in to the app. Should be set both in sign-up and sign-in tests.

        This user is returned by TestAuth.TestAuthService.getUser()

      • testAuthError

        public static AuthService.AuthError testAuthError
        The intended AuthService.AuthError during sign-in and sing-up error tests.

        This auth error is returned by TestAuth.TestAuthService.getAuthError() and is sent to observers by TestAuth.TestAuthService.signUp(String, String, String) or TestAuth.TestAuthService.signIn(String, String) when one of successUserSignedUp or successUserSignedIn is false

      • isTestUserSignedIn

        public static boolean isTestUserSignedIn
        Set to true when sign-in or sign-up is required for the test.

        This boolean is returned by TestAuth.TestAuthService.isUserSignedIn()}

      • successUserSignedUp

        public static boolean successUserSignedUp
        Set to true when testing that a user signed up successfully. Set false when testing sign-up errors.

        When this is true, this TestAuthService will call AuthServiceObserver.onUserSignedUp(IUser) with argument testAuthUser

        When this is false, this TestAuthService will call AuthServiceObserver.onAuthSignUpError(AuthService.AuthError) with argument testAuthError

      • successUserSignedIn

        public static boolean successUserSignedIn
        Set to true when testing that user sign in successfully. Set false when testing sign-in errors.

        When this is true, this TestAuthService will call AuthServiceObserver.onUserSignedIn(IUser) with argument testAuthUser

        When this is false, this TestAuthService will call AuthServiceObserver.onAuthSignInError(AuthService.AuthError) with argument testAuthError
